---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="Who's behind Duckgineer, what we cover, and why it exists.">

  <!-- Hero banner -->
  <div class="about-hero">
    <img class="about-hero__bg" src="/images/about-banner.png" alt="" aria-hidden="true" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" />
    <div class="about-hero__overlay"></div>
    <div class="about-hero__inner">
      <div class="about-hero__badge">est. 2026</div>
      <h1 class="about-hero__title"><span class="logo-text__engineer">Duck</span><span class="logo-text__forge">gineer</span></h1>
      <p class="about-hero__tagline">Where Engineers Talk, AI Thinks.</p>
      <p class="about-hero__sub">
        A real engineer's public lab showing how AI is used in software engineering workflows.<br/>
        Some experiments worked. Some didn't. All of it ended up here.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Manifesto cards -->
  <div class="about-manifesto reveal-stagger">
    <div class="about-manifesto__card reveal">
      <span class="about-manifesto__icon">⚡</span>
      <h3>Production or it didn't happen</h3>
      <p>Every technique here has been run against real code, real APIs, and real cost constraints. No demos. No vibes.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-manifesto__card reveal">
      <span class="about-manifesto__icon">💸</span>
      <h3>Tokens cost money</h3>
      <p>We track what we spend, optimize what we can, and publish the numbers — even when they're embarrassing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-manifesto__card reveal">
      <span class="about-manifesto__icon">🔥</span>
      <h3>Failures ship too</h3>
      <p>If a prompt blew up, a model hallucinated, or an approach wasted a week — that's a post. Failure has better signal.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- What's covered -->
  <div class="about-section reveal">
    <h2 class="about-section__title">What we cover</h2>
    <div class="about-topics">
      <div class="about-topic">
        <span class="about-topic__tag" style="background:rgba(245,197,24,0.15);color:#F5C518">#claude</span>
        <p>Prompt engineering, Claude Code, Claude CLI — what actually works in CI pipelines and production codebases.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-topic">
        <span class="about-topic__tag" style="background:rgba(236,72,153,0.15);color:#f472b6">#engineering</span>
        <p>AI-assisted engineering workflows across SW and HW — code generation, automation, getting LLMs to stop making things up.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-topic">
        <span class="about-topic__tag" style="background:rgba(6,182,212,0.15);color:#22d3ee">#opentap</span>
        <p>Test automation with OpenTAP — using AI to generate, validate, and debug test steps without losing your mind.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-topic">
        <span class="about-topic__tag" style="background:rgba(251,146,60,0.15);color:#fb923c">#token-optimization</span>
        <p>Cutting API costs without cutting quality. Context window tricks, prompt compression, caching strategies.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-topic">
        <span class="about-topic__tag" style="background:rgba(34,211,238,0.15);color:#22d3ee">#ci-cd</span>
        <p>AI review gates, automated test generation, LLM-powered pipelines that ship faster and break less.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-topic">
        <span class="about-topic__tag" style="background:rgba(74,222,128,0.15);color:#4ade80">#workflow</span>
        <p>Day-to-day engineering with AI — the habits, tools, and shortcuts that have stuck after months of use.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Author -->
  <div class="about-author reveal">
    <div class="about-author__avatar">
      <span>🧑‍💻</span>
    </div>
    <div class="about-author__bio">
      <h2>Who's driving</h2>
      <p>
        A software and hardware engineer with a habit of asking "can AI do this?" — and then actually finding out.
      </p>
      <p>
        I work across SW and HW engineering — systems, automation, integration. Over the past year I've been embedding AI
        into real workflows: not as a gimmick, but as something the team actually uses daily. That means building AI solutions,
        running experiments that sometimes blow up, and leading engineers through the "wait, this actually works?" moment.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of work I'm here — running the same experiments in public, writing up what I find, and being honest when
        something doesn't work out the way I planned. Favourite tools right now: Claude, Codex, and OpenTAP.
        Least favourite thing: AI blog posts with no actual prompts in them. (Hence this site.)
      </p>
      <p>
        Duckgineer started as notes-to-self. It became a blog when the notes got too useful to keep in a Teams chat that nobody reads.
      </p>
      <a href="/posts/why-i-built-applied-claude-lab" class="about-author__link">Why I Am Building Duckgineer →</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
/* ── About Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.about-hero {
  position: relative; overflow: hidden;
  margin: -2rem -3rem 0;
  padding: 6rem 3rem 4.5rem;
}

.about-hero__bg {
  position: absolute; inset: 0;
  width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover;
  opacity: 0.3;
}

.about-hero__overlay {
  position: absolute; inset: 0;
  background: linear-gradient(
    135deg,
    rgba(9,9,11,0.95) 0%,
    rgba(9,9,11,0.75) 50%,
    rgba(9,9,11,0.35) 100%
  );
}

.about-hero__inner { position: relative; z-index: 1; max-width: 640px; }

.about-hero__badge {
  display: inline-block;
  font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--accent); border: 1px solid rgba(245,197,24,0.4);
  padding: 3px 12px; border-radius: 999px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.about-hero__title {
  font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
  font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.06em; line-height: 1.15;
  background: var(--gradient-text);
  -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  padding-bottom: 0.15em;
}

.about-hero__tagline {
  font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--accent);
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}

.about-hero__sub {
  font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.75;
}

/* ── Manifesto cards ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.about-manifesto {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1.25rem;
  margin: 3rem 0;
}

.about-manifesto__card {
  background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 14px; padding: 1.75rem;
  transition: all 0.25s var(--ease);
}
.about-manifesto__card:hover { border-color: var(--border-hover); box-shadow: var(--shadow-glow); transform: translateY(-2px); }

.about-manifesto__icon { font-size: 1.75rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.85rem; }

.about-manifesto__card h3 {
  font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--text);
}
.about-manifesto__card p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-3); line-height: 1.65; }

/* ── About section ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.about-section { margin: 3.5rem 0; }

.about-section__title {
  font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
}

.about-topics {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1.25rem;
}

.about-topic {
  background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem;
  transition: all 0.25s var(--ease);
}
.about-topic:hover { border-color: var(--border-hover); box-shadow: var(--shadow-glow); }

.about-topic__tag {
  display: inline-block; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700;
  padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 999px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}
.about-topic p { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-3); line-height: 1.65; }

/* ── Author ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.about-author {
  display: flex; gap: 2rem; align-items: flex-start;
  background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 16px; padding: 2.25rem; margin: 3.5rem 0;
  transition: border-color 0.25s;
}
.about-author:hover { border-color: var(--border-hover); }

.about-author__avatar {
  width: 72px; height: 72px; flex-shrink: 0;
  background: var(--gradient-subtle);
  border: 2px solid rgba(245,197,24,0.3);
  border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  font-size: 2rem;
}

.about-author__bio h2 {
  font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
}
.about-author__bio p { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

.about-author__link {
  display: inline-block; margin-top: 0.5rem;
  font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(245,197,24,0.35);
  padding-bottom: 1px;
  transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s;
}
.about-author__link:hover { color: var(--accent-light, #c4b5fd); border-color: var(--accent); }

/* ── Responsive ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .about-manifesto { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
}
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .about-hero { margin: -1.5rem -1.25rem 0; padding: 3.5rem 1.25rem 3rem; }
  .about-manifesto { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .about-topics { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .about-author { flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; }
}
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .about-hero { margin: -1.25rem -1rem 0; padding: 2.5rem 1rem 2rem; }
}
</style>
